President Trump's weekly address focuses on tax cuts and reform. He outlines four principles for tax reform: simplifying the tax code, cutting taxes for the middle class, making the tax system more attractive for investment and job creation, and bringing back wealth parked overseas. Trump emphasizes the importance of American families and their interests, stating that tax reform should benefit American workers and businesses. He calls for bipartisan cooperation in passing historic tax reform and tax cuts. Trump believes that these measures will lead to unprecedented prosperity and make America great again.